      "applicationProcess": [
        {
          "mode": "Offline",
          "process": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Step 1: The applicant has to visit the Sarpanch of Gram Panchayat and other elected public representatives to collect the application forms for crop demonstration participation."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Step 2: Complete the application forms with accurate details about your farming experience, land size, crops grown, and willingness to adopt new techniques."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Step 3: Submit the filled-out application forms to the Agriculture Supervisor at the designated office or during the scheduled meeting with the Sarpanch and other public representatives."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Step 4: After submitting your application, await the selection process. The Agriculture Supervisor will compile a list of eligible farmers, ensuring it is three times more than the target."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Step 5: Once the list is prepared, eligible farmers will participate in a lottery selection process, conducted in the presence of relevant officials. If chosen, you will be notified of your selection for the crop demonstration."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "process_md": "Step 1: The applicant has to visit the Sarpanch of Gram Panchayat and other elected public representatives to collect the application forms for crop demonstration participation.\n<br>\n\nStep 2: Complete the application forms with accurate details about your farming experience, land size, crops grown, and willingness to adopt new techniques.\n<br>\n\nStep 3: Submit the filled-out application forms to the Agriculture Supervisor at the designated office or during the scheduled meeting with the Sarpanch and other public representatives.\n<br>\n\nStep 4: After submitting your application, await the selection process. The Agriculture Supervisor will compile a list of eligible farmers, ensuring it is three times more than the target.\n<br>\n\nStep 5: Once the list is prepared, eligible farmers will participate in a lottery selection process, conducted in the presence of relevant officials. If chosen, you will be notified of your selection for the crop demonstration.\n<br>\n\n"
        }
      ],
      "schemeDefinitions": [],
      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. Farmers who can bear the additional cost as per departmental recommendations and need, along with the assistance provided under the scheme.\n1. The selected demonstration area must have irrigation facilities apart from dryland farming.\n1. Only one member from a farmer&#39;s family will be given the opportunity for demonstration.\n1. The demonstration will be organized at the block level.\n1. The selected seeds, fertilizers, and other inputs must be used as per the guidelines.\n1. A farmer can set up a demonstration plot on a maximum of 1 hectare, but it can also be on less than 1 hectare on a pro-rata basis.\n1. In the National Food Security Mission, the farmer&#39;s plot must be at least 0.4 hectares.\n1. Farmers who have not benefited from crop demonstration programs in the past three years are eligible.\n\n",
